16
00:02:22,905 --> 00:02:25,905
of a massacre that was about to happen.

17
00:02:25,905 --> 00:02:31,005
Ran calls Shinichi to get help on deciphering the code.

18
00:02:31,005 --> 00:02:32,131
But during the conversation,

19
00:02:32,305 --> 00:02:34,133
I realized that the first sentence of the coded note

20
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:38,137
was referring to the famous clock tower, Big Ben,

21
00:02:38,137 --> 00:02:41,805
and carelessly told her what I realized, in Shinichi's voice.

22
00:02:43,505 --> 00:02:46,145
Since Ran firmly believed that Shinichi is also in London,

23
00:02:46,145 --> 00:02:47,705
she persistently pursues me,

24
00:02:47,705 --> 00:02:49,305
so I had no choice but to...

25
00:02:53,605 --> 00:02:59,305
"Sherlock Holmes' Revelation (Satan)"

26
00:02:59,705 --> 00:03:02,805
From right about after he got the call from Ran last night,

27
00:03:02,805 --> 00:03:05,205
he suddenly started shaking...

28
00:03:06,405 --> 00:03:10,169
Since he ran around the city of London all sweaty,

29
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:11,805
then got cold in the night wind,

30
00:03:11,805 --> 00:03:13,305
maybe he caught a cold.

31
00:03:13,305 --> 00:03:15,505
Oh boy. I mean we're going to be

32
00:03:15,505 --> 00:03:17,905
leaving for Japan tomorrow night already, and then...

33
00:03:17,905 --> 00:03:19,805
Well, he drank his medicine

34
00:03:19,805 --> 00:03:22,181
and his fever is coming down, too.

35
00:03:22,181 --> 00:03:24,505
So if he sleeps a day, he'll be fine!

36
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:26,185
So...

37
00:03:26,185 --> 00:03:28,187
Don't worry about me.

38
00:03:28,405 --> 00:03:32,705
Ran and Pops, please decipher that code!

39
00:03:32,705 --> 00:03:34,505
The seven sentences in that coded memo

40
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:40,199
is each probably some building somewhere or a place!

41
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:42,201
How do you know?

42
00:03:42,201 --> 00:03:46,605
Shinichi told me so.

43
00:03:46,605 --> 00:03:48,207
Shinichi did...

44
00:03:49,905 --> 00:03:53,505
By the way, Shinichi was saying in front of Big Ben

45
00:03:53,505 --> 00:03:56,905
that the first line that goes, "The loud ringing of the bell",

46
00:03:56,905 --> 00:03:58,705
means the chime of Big Ben.

47
00:03:58,705 --> 00:04:00,705
In front of Big Ben...

48
00:04:00,705 --> 00:04:04,223
You mean that detective kid is here in London?

49
00:04:04,223 --> 00:04:07,205
I mean, you knew about it, eh?

50
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:10,805
If I knew, I wouldn't have made a gift list!

51
00:04:10,805 --> 00:04:15,205
At any rate, just leave Conan to me.

52
00:04:15,205 --> 00:04:19,905
Ran and Kogoro, go ahead and decipher the code, all right?

53
00:04:24,605 --> 00:04:26,805
We somehow managed to get through.

54
00:04:26,805 --> 00:04:29,905
But I didn't think you'd go as far as to drink the antidote

55
00:04:29,905 --> 00:04:31,705
