70
00:05:03,105 --> 00:05:05,305
when my body will turn into Conan again!

71
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:10,005
Beside, I really can't face up to her right now.

72
00:05:11,205 --> 00:05:12,805
More important, look at this.

73
00:05:12,805 --> 00:05:15,105
-This morning's paper. -Huh?

74
00:05:15,105 --> 00:05:16,295
From the fingerprints that were detected

75
00:05:16,295 --> 00:05:18,705
on the piece of paper with the code written on it,

76
00:05:18,705 --> 00:05:21,605
they seemed to have come up with a suspect!

77
00:05:21,605 --> 00:05:23,705
His name is Hades Sabara.

78
00:05:23,705 --> 00:05:25,805
He's a serial killer on the run!

79
00:05:27,205 --> 00:05:30,105
First, we've got to investigate on this guy.

80
00:05:30,105 --> 00:05:32,905
But, if they've come up with a culprit,

81
00:05:32,905 --> 00:05:34,313
I'm sure he'll soon be arrested.

82
00:05:34,505 --> 00:05:36,005
Come on!

83
00:05:36,005 --> 00:05:39,505
This guy deliberately left his fingerprints behind, you know?

84
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:41,005
Which means he's planning to do something,

85
00:05:41,005 --> 00:05:43,205
despite risking being arrested!

86
00:05:45,105 --> 00:05:48,327
If you say that the loud ringing bell is Big Ben,

87
00:05:48,327 --> 00:05:50,972
it's quite convincing.

88
00:05:50,972 --> 00:05:54,333
But there can't possibly be buildings

89
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:56,335
that look like eggs or pickles.

90
00:05:56,572 --> 00:05:58,337
-Excuse me! -Yes?

91
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:03,672
Is there an egg-shaped building here in London?

92
00:06:03,672 --> 00:06:07,472
Oh yes, there's a city hall near the Tower Bridge.

93
00:06:07,472 --> 00:06:08,972
It's there!

94
00:06:10,072 --> 00:06:14,072
"London City Hall"

95
00:06:14,072 --> 00:06:15,172
It's unbelievable that

96
00:06:15,172 --> 00:06:17,772
there would be a building shaped like this.

97
00:06:17,772 --> 00:06:20,072
Then, for the 3rd sentence that goes...

98
00:06:20,072 --> 00:06:22,361
"Fill an empty stomach on a boiled egg

99
00:06:22,361 --> 00:06:24,363
as cold as a corpse" would mean...

100
00:06:24,572 --> 00:06:26,365
this City Hall here!

101
00:06:26,365 --> 00:06:29,672
What are these words? A code?

102
00:06:30,972 --> 00:06:33,672
Do they mean a name?

103
00:06:33,672 --> 00:06:36,375
The doll's name is Mazarin Stone!

104
00:06:36,572 --> 00:06:38,377
Mazarin Stone...

105
00:06:38,377 --> 00:06:40,379
Mazarin Stone!

106
00:06:40,379 --> 00:06:42,372
Hi!

107
00:06:42,372 --> 00:06:44,383
How did you get the doll?

108
00:06:44,383 --> 00:06:48,387
The doll? I found it there beside the bench,

109
00:06:48,387 --> 00:06:50,389
under the shrubs.

110
00:06:50,572 --> 00:06:52,772
Can I see that?

111
00:06:52,772 --> 00:06:54,672
You can keep it!

112
00:06:54,672 --> 00:06:57,472
I've got plenty already!

113
00:06:57,472 --> 00:06:59,372
-Goodbye! -Goodbye!

114
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:02,172
What's that?

115
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:05,472
It may have something to do with the code!

116
00:07:05,472 --> 00:07:06,672
You see,

117
00:07:06,672 --> 00:07:10,172
the culprit who was passing out the paper with the code

118
00:07:10,172 --> 00:07:14,413
said, "If you can't solve it, ask Holmes", right?

119
00:07:14,413 --> 00:07:17,672
If so, he may have scattered things

120
00:07:17,672 --> 00:07:19,472
that have to do with Holmes near the places

121
00:07:19,472 --> 00:07:22,421
indicated by the code, don't you think?

122
00:07:22,421 --> 00:07:25,072
Shinichi told me some time ago,

123
00:07:25,072 --> 00:07:29,072
that "Mazarin Stone" is the titles of one of Holmes' story.

124
00:07:29,072 --> 00:07:33,772
Hey, I went out of my way to make you lunch,

125
00:07:33,772 --> 00:07:36,172
but you haven't touched it at all!

126
00:07:36,172 --> 00:07:39,372
Sorry, I was just checking on a case

127
00:07:39,372 --> 00:07:41,672
that Inspector Megure told me to investigate.

128
00:07:41,672 --> 00:07:43,572
Geez!

129
00:07:43,572 --> 00:07:45,072
Getting carried away making deductions

130
00:07:45,072 --> 00:07:47,972
to point of forgetting that you're hungry.

131
00:07:47,972 --> 00:07:50,472
You're going to starve to death one day!

132
00:07:50,472 --> 00:07:54,772
In a story called Mazarin Stone, Holmes said,

133
00:07:54,772 --> 00:07:59,772
"The brain works better on an empty stomach!"

134
00:07:59,772 --> 00:08:02,172
Holmes again?

135
00:08:02,172 --> 00:08:05,772
"I'm all brains, Watson."

136
00:08:06,772 --> 00:08:09,472
"The rest is just a continuation of add-on sentences!"

137
00:08:11,272 --> 00:08:14,172
If only the top part of the sentences is important...

138
00:08:15,472 --> 00:08:18,477
The head part is what is important.

139
00:08:19,872 --> 00:08:22,172
Hey, just what're you doing?

140
00:08:22,172 --> 00:08:24,483
Huh? Something's written!

141
00:08:24,483 --> 00:08:25,872
What?

142
00:08:25,872 --> 00:08:27,272
T.

143
00:08:27,272 --> 00:08:28,772
T?

144
00:08:28,772 --> 00:08:30,489
I get it!

145
00:08:30,672 --> 00:08:33,972
Some alphabets are hidden in the places indicated by the code,

146
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:36,072
and if connected the alphabets,

147
00:08:36,072 --> 00:08:38,497
probably form words. What do you think?

148
00:08:38,497 --> 00:08:42,501
But after the "egg" is the "pickle", right?

149
00:08:42,501 --> 00:08:45,272
A thin, flat building that looks like a pickle

150
00:08:45,272 --> 00:08:48,172
couldn't possibly exist.

151
00:08:48,172 --> 00:08:52,511
But the code said "Bite on the whole pickle."

152
00:08:52,511 --> 00:08:54,872
So, it must be pickles before they are sliced.

153
00:08:54,872 --> 00:08:56,515
Don't be silly!

154
00:08:56,515 --> 00:09:00,872
Pickles are young cucumbers immersed in vinegar, you know!

155
00:09:00,872 --> 00:09:03,972
There's no way that such a long, narrow, round building

156
00:09:03,972 --> 00:09:05,872
could exist in this world, you see...

157
00:09:12,272 --> 00:09:14,533
That must be the one!

158
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:15,872
No way!

159
00:09:16,535 --> 00:09:20,539
This Hades Sabara guy is really dangerous.

160
00:09:20,772 --> 00:09:23,972
He seems to have started off as a serious office worker

161
00:09:23,972 --> 00:09:25,972
but after his mother fell ill, of a rare disease,

162
00:09:25,972 --> 00:09:27,972
he went out and borrowed money from his acquaintances

163
00:09:27,972 --> 00:09:30,549
to gather funds for his mother's surgery.

164
00:09:30,549 --> 00:09:32,551
Then he invested the money into stocks and bookies,

165
00:09:32,551 --> 00:09:34,553
but lost everything.

166
00:09:34,553 --> 00:09:37,272
Because of this, his mother couldn't undergo surgery,

167
00:09:37,272 --> 00:09:39,672
and she passed away last year in July.

168
00:09:39,672 --> 00:09:43,772
He slaughtered one man after the other,

169
00:09:43,772 --> 00:09:45,672
not only his acquaintances

170
00:09:45,672 --> 00:09:47,572
who kept hounding him for collection,

171
00:09:47,572 --> 00:09:52,072
but also the people who suggested that he invest in stocks.

172
00:09:52,072 --> 00:09:54,272
On top of that, he blew up the hospitals

173
00:09:54,272 --> 00:09:57,272
that refused to perform surgery on his mother one after the other,

174
00:09:57,272 --> 00:09:59,872
which resulted in a large number of casualties.

175
00:09:59,872 --> 00:10:01,672
Blew up...

176
00:10:01,672 --> 00:10:03,472
You mean he uses bombs, too?

177
00:10:03,472 --> 00:10:04,583
Yeah.

178
00:10:04,583 --> 00:10:06,872
While Hades was on the run,

179
00:10:06,872 --> 00:10:08,587
he ran into a woman named Hestia,

180
00:10:08,587 --> 00:10:11,972
a military outcast and expert on explosives.

181
00:10:11,972 --> 00:10:14,593
She helped Hades carry out his revenge!

182
00:10:15,672 --> 00:10:17,572
As for that woman,

183
00:10:17,572 --> 00:10:21,072
it says that she blew herself up

184
00:10:21,072 --> 00:10:23,572
when the police found her at her hide-out.

185
00:10:23,572 --> 00:10:25,872
But since her body seems to have blown to pieces...

186
00:10:25,872 --> 00:10:27,872
You mean the body that turned up was of someone else,

187
00:10:27,872 --> 00:10:30,609
and that she is still alive?

188
00:10:30,609 --> 00:10:31,772
Yeah.

189
00:10:31,772 --> 00:10:34,613
But why is it that such a vicious criminal

190
00:10:34,772 --> 00:10:36,972
still remains on the loose?

191
00:10:36,972 --> 00:10:38,617
It seems that he's gone through

192
00:10:38,617 --> 00:10:40,272
repeated plastic surgeries while on the run.

193
00:10:40,272 --> 00:10:44,623
Well, with this guy, you can never tell what he'll do.

194
00:10:44,623 --> 00:10:46,625
After all, he may have a grudge

195
00:10:46,872 --> 00:10:48,627
against the entire country of Great Britain

196
00:10:48,627 --> 00:10:52,631
which allows bookies to prey on anybody, in every way possible.

197
00:10:57,472 --> 00:10:59,172
It's from Ran.

198
00:11:01,972 --> 00:11:04,372
Sorry. Answer it for me, will you?

199
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:08,372
Huh? It'll be strange if I answer that phone!

200
00:11:08,372 --> 00:11:10,672
I mean, hurry up and answer it!

201
00:11:10,672 --> 00:11:14,372
She could've come up with something concerning the code!

202
00:11:14,372 --> 00:11:15,772
True.

203
00:11:17,372 --> 00:11:19,072
-Hello? -If you're there,

204
00:11:19,072 --> 00:11:21,172
hurry up and answer the phone, stupid!

205
00:11:21,172 --> 00:11:24,663
That's Ran's cell phone, isn't it?

206
00:11:24,663 --> 00:11:27,672
Ran's all blushed and couldn't work up the courage to call you,

207
00:11:27,672 --> 00:11:30,669
