243
00:12:56,172 --> 00:12:58,772
The scratches will most likely match up in a certain place.

244
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:03,672
I found it! It's the letter N!

245
00:13:03,672 --> 00:13:05,872
But, how did you know?

246
00:13:05,872 --> 00:13:09,372
He said so in the story!

247
00:13:09,372 --> 00:13:12,272
"Get rid of all the deductions part way,

248
00:13:12,272 --> 00:13:15,972
and indicate only the starting point and the conclusion.

249
00:13:15,972 --> 00:13:17,572
Though it may seem meretricious,

250
00:13:17,572 --> 00:13:20,772
it will have a sufficiently surprising effect!"

251
00:13:20,772 --> 00:13:24,783
I see! That's why the barrel in the middle

252
00:13:24,783 --> 00:13:27,772
had to be taken away before matching top and bottom caps together!

253
00:13:27,772 --> 00:13:30,172
Then, maybe there's something near Big Ben

254
00:13:30,172 --> 00:13:33,272
that was mentioned in the beginning too?

255
00:13:33,272 --> 00:13:35,872
I thought so too and came here,

256
00:13:35,872 --> 00:13:38,472
but I can't find anything.

257
00:13:38,472 --> 00:13:40,799
There's a strange arrow drawn on the road

258
00:13:40,972 --> 00:13:44,572
in front of the gate of Big Ben that dad found, but...

259
00:13:44,572 --> 00:13:46,572
-An arrow? -Yep.

260
00:13:46,572 --> 00:13:49,472
You know that there's a bridge right beside Big Ben, right?

261
00:13:49,472 --> 00:13:51,672
It seems to be pointing in that direction.

262
00:13:54,172 --> 00:13:55,472
I get it!

263
00:13:57,572 --> 00:13:59,072
Part way across the bridge

264
00:13:59,072 --> 00:14:00,572
beside the drain with the lid removed,

265
00:14:00,572 --> 00:14:02,472
there was something written.

266
00:14:02,472 --> 00:14:05,172
The Valley of Fear.

267
00:14:05,172 --> 00:14:07,672
It's The Valley of Fear!

268
00:14:07,672 --> 00:14:10,072
I found it! I found it, Shinichi!

269
00:14:10,072 --> 00:14:12,831
Where is the keyword hidden?

270
00:14:12,831 --> 00:14:14,833
The Valley of Fear...

271
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,835
It was a long story.

272
00:14:16,835 --> 00:14:19,772
I wonder if any bridge came out in that story?

273
00:14:19,772 --> 00:14:22,572
No, it doesn't necessarily have to be a bridge.

274
00:14:22,572 --> 00:14:26,472
A drain... river... water...

275
00:14:26,472 --> 00:14:27,672
Water?

276
00:14:27,672 --> 00:14:30,072
Don't you see anything in the river?

277
00:14:30,072 --> 00:14:31,372
Huh?

278
00:14:31,372 --> 00:14:34,872
"If something heavy is gone near the water,

279
00:14:34,872 --> 00:14:39,572
there's no doubt that something was sunk into the water."

280
00:14:39,572 --> 00:14:41,672
This is Holmes' dialogue.

281
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:45,272
That's why I think that there's something sunk into the Thames.

282
00:14:48,372 --> 00:14:50,869
On the lamppost that is on the railing of the bridge...

283
00:14:50,869 --> 00:14:52,672
There is a thin rope tied on,

284
00:14:52,672 --> 00:14:55,372
and the tip of the rope is sunk into the river!

285
00:15:05,272 --> 00:15:08,272
It's the alphabet "A"! "A" is carved on it!

286
00:15:08,272 --> 00:15:11,472
So, the letters you found are T, N, and A.

287
00:15:11,472 --> 00:15:12,891
Hey, Shinichi.

288
00:15:13,072 --> 00:15:17,372
I think the next place is going to be something like a cake,

289
00:15:17,372 --> 00:15:19,472
but where should I go?

290
00:15:20,899 --> 00:15:22,901
Talking on the phone is getting us nowhere!

291
00:15:22,901 --> 00:15:25,472
You wait there, because I'll be right over!

292
00:15:33,841 --> 00:15:35,941
The phone will do just fine.

293
00:15:35,941 --> 00:15:38,917
You see, we somehow managed to find

294
00:15:38,917 --> 00:15:40,919
the 3 keywords up to now, too.

295
00:15:40,919 --> 00:15:44,941
Huh? If that detective kid is here in London,

296
00:15:44,941 --> 00:15:47,441
wouldn't it be faster if we got together

297
00:15:47,441 --> 00:15:48,927
and solved the code with him?

298
00:15:49,141 --> 00:15:53,841
Or, do you have a reason for not wanting him to come?

299
00:15:53,841 --> 00:15:55,341
No, it's nothing like that!

300
00:15:55,341 --> 00:15:56,935
Oh?

301
00:15:56,935 --> 00:15:58,941
You're the girl I ran into yesterday!

302
00:15:58,941 --> 00:16:01,641
Minerva Grass!

303
00:16:01,641 --> 00:16:04,741
Minerva Grass, that tennis player?

304
00:16:04,741 --> 00:16:06,945
Is it alright for you to be walking around outside?

305
00:16:06,945 --> 00:16:09,841
The finals for the ladies' single match is tomorrow, isn't it?

306
00:16:09,841 --> 00:16:13,541
Yes. I'm taking a break from training right now.

307
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:15,441
Are you all right?

308
00:16:15,441 --> 00:16:17,641
The thing that was bothering you last night.

309
00:16:17,641 --> 00:16:20,941
Don't tell me that he's your boyfriend?

310
00:16:20,941 --> 00:16:22,961
He's my father.

311
00:16:22,961 --> 00:16:26,441
Besides, I'm more concerned over the code right now.

312
00:16:26,441 --> 00:16:27,941
Code?

313
00:16:27,941 --> 00:16:30,741
Then, it's the same as my younger brother Apollo!

314
00:16:30,741 --> 00:16:32,741
My brother received a piece of paper from a strange man,

315
00:16:32,741 --> 00:16:34,141
and seems to have given that paper with codes written on it

316
00:16:34,141 --> 00:16:36,441
to a boy who claimed to be Holmes' disciple.

317
00:16:36,441 --> 00:16:38,641
Holmes' disciple?

318
00:16:38,641 --> 00:16:40,741
I think his name was Conan.

319
00:16:40,741 --> 00:16:41,941
I see!

320
00:16:41,941 --> 00:16:44,983
The Apollo that Conan was talking about was you!

321
00:16:45,141 --> 00:16:47,841
Huh? Do you know him?

322
00:16:47,841 --> 00:16:48,987
Yes.

323
00:16:48,987 --> 00:16:52,241
But today's he's sleeping back at the hotel because of a cold.

324
00:16:53,741 --> 00:16:55,741
Did you hear that? Shinichi!

325
00:16:55,741 --> 00:16:57,841
I coincidentally ran into a boy named Apollo

326
00:16:57,841 --> 00:17:01,641
that gave the paper with the code on it to Conan.

327
00:17:01,641 --> 00:17:03,001
Shinichi?

328
00:17:03,001 --> 00:17:05,003
Sorry.

329
00:17:05,003 --> 00:17:08,241
I've come up with an urgent matter,

330
00:17:08,241 --> 00:17:11,541
and can't go over there.

331
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:13,011
Is that so?

332
00:17:13,011 --> 00:17:16,541
Yeah. I just got mail from a client of another case

333
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:19,741
who says he's coming over to see me now.

334
00:17:19,741 --> 00:17:22,241
Well, if it's urgent, it can't be helped.

335
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:24,041
Well, I'll be at the hotel,

336
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:26,241
so just call me anytime!

337
00:17:26,241 --> 00:17:27,841
The one sending out the code

338
00:17:27,841 --> 00:17:30,541
is a nefarious criminal called Hades Sabara,

339
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:33,441
we've got to decipher the code as soon as possible.

340
00:17:33,441 --> 00:17:35,033
If that boy Apollo is with you,

341
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:36,541
have him go around with you!

342
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:39,037
Because I'm sure that he knows London more than you two do!

343
00:17:39,037 --> 00:17:41,441
Okay, I got you!

344
00:17:42,541 --> 00:17:44,341
You know what, Apollo!

345
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:46,541
Will you come along and help us decipher the code?

346
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:48,341
Yep! Okay!

347
00:17:48,341 --> 00:17:50,441
I'll be at the hotel.

348
00:17:50,441 --> 00:17:52,641
I've got a masseur coming.

349
00:17:52,641 --> 00:17:55,641
Please take good care of him!

350
00:17:55,641 --> 00:17:57,041
Sure thing!

351
00:17:58,841 --> 00:18:02,141
But the next code is cake, isn't it?

352
00:18:02,141 --> 00:18:05,641
Is there a building in London that's shaped like that?

353
00:18:05,641 --> 00:18:07,065
Cake?

354
00:18:07,065 --> 00:18:08,541
Yep, I know where it is!

355
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:09,641
-Huh? -Huh?

356
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:15,841
Wow! It really looks like a wedding cake!

357
00:18:15,841 --> 00:18:17,841
Of course it looks just like one!

358
00:18:17,841 --> 00:18:19,741
The wedding cake is said to have been designed

359
00:18:19,741 --> 00:18:22,441
after the shape of this church!

360
00:18:22,441 --> 00:18:25,541
Even the name is St. Bride Church.

361
00:18:25,541 --> 00:18:27,841
It really sounds like a joke.

362
00:18:27,841 --> 00:18:30,341
Apollo, I'm amazed you knew about it!

363
00:18:30,341 --> 00:18:33,441
It's because big sis used to bring me here a lot.

364
00:18:33,441 --> 00:18:36,141
She says that she going to get married to Ales

365
00:18:36,141 --> 00:18:37,841
one day at this church.

366
00:18:37,841 --> 00:18:39,441
Who's Ales?

367
00:18:39,441 --> 00:18:41,441
Big sis' ex-coach!

368
00:18:41,441 --> 00:18:45,641
Daddy used to be Ales' coach before though!

369
00:18:45,641 --> 00:18:48,741
Your father died in a traffic accident.

370
00:18:48,741 --> 00:18:52,541
Yep! On his way to watch Ales' match.

371
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:56,341
Big sis was at home that day with mother because of a cold,

372
00:18:56,341 --> 00:18:59,641
and I was still in mother's stomach back then.

373
00:18:59,641 --> 00:19:01,141
That's why I heard that Ales...

374
00:19:01,141 --> 00:19:02,741
suddenly retired from being a player

375
00:19:02,741 --> 00:19:06,041
and became big sis' coach!

376
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:09,127
Because it seems to have been daddy's dream

377
00:19:09,127 --> 00:19:11,841
to make big sis a winner at the Wimbledon!

378
00:19:11,841 --> 00:19:13,941
Then, his dream has been granted!

379
00:19:13,941 --> 00:19:15,133
Yep!

380
00:19:15,341 --> 00:19:21,641
But Ales still blames himself for the death of daddy.

381
00:19:21,641 --> 00:19:24,141
So, he got into a fight with big sis

382
00:19:24,141 --> 00:19:26,241
and quit being her coach.

383
00:19:26,241 --> 00:19:29,141
I know that Ales likes big sis too, and yet...

384
00:19:29,141 --> 00:19:31,541
He's bluffing being strong saying stuff like, "In Tennis, love is zero.

385
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,151
No matter how much you accumulate on zero,

386
00:19:33,151 --> 00:19:37,155
all you get from it is defeat."

387
00:19:37,155 --> 00:19:39,841
In tennis, love is zero.

388
00:19:39,841 --> 00:19:42,741
I see. That's why she said what she did.

389
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:47,441
Then, you're troubled over love?

390
00:19:47,441 --> 00:19:50,841
But I'm no longer troubled, though.

391
00:19:50,841 --> 00:19:53,941
Love is zero.

392
00:19:53,941 --> 00:19:55,941
No matter how many zeros you accumulate,

393
00:19:55,941 --> 00:19:57,941
the result is miserable defeat.

394
00:20:01,441 --> 00:20:04,541
Rather, I completely forgot to tell her

395
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:06,441
what I was supposed to!

396
00:20:06,441 --> 00:20:09,187
Who are you going to tell what to?

397
00:20:09,341 --> 00:20:10,541
It's nothing.

398
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:12,941
Don't we have to look for it?

399
00:20:12,941 --> 00:20:16,341
Somewhere in this church there is a hidden keyword

400
00:20:16,341 --> 00:20:18,541
that has something to do with Holmes, right?

401
00:20:18,541 --> 00:20:21,199
Right. We've got to look for it!

402
00:20:26,841 --> 00:20:29,941
"A Scandal in Bohemia"

403
00:20:29,941 --> 00:20:31,209
What?

404
00:20:31,209 --> 00:20:33,541
You found paper on the ground around the church

405
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:35,641
that was shaped like a wedding cake?

406
00:20:35,641 --> 00:20:38,241
And? What's written on the paper?

407
00:20:38,241 --> 00:20:40,141
It's handwritten and reads...

408
00:20:40,141 --> 00:20:43,221
"A Scandal in Bohemia."

409
00:20:43,221 --> 00:20:45,641
A Scandal in Bohemia...

410
00:20:45,641 --> 00:20:48,441
is the story that Irene Adler appears in.

411
00:20:48,441 --> 00:20:50,441
And, is there anything besides the title

412
00:20:50,441 --> 00:20:52,041
that is written on that paper

413
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:53,841
or is there something strange about it?

414
00:20:53,841 --> 00:20:56,341
The color of the paper is light pink

415
00:20:56,341 --> 00:20:59,541
and the words seem to be written in black ink.

416
00:20:59,541 --> 00:21:03,241
There's nothing else strange about it.

417
00:21:03,241 --> 00:21:05,741
The paper is thick and you can't see through it.

418
00:21:05,741 --> 00:21:07,941
You can't tell because you're just looking at it

419
00:21:07,941 --> 00:21:09,941
and not really scrutinizing it.

420
00:21:09,941 --> 00:21:13,251
How rude! I am scrutinizing it!

421
00:21:13,251 --> 00:21:14,241
No.

422
00:21:14,241 --> 00:21:15,841
That's the dialogue that

423
00:21:15,841 --> 00:21:18,641
Holmes said to Watson in that story.

424
00:21:18,641 --> 00:21:19,941
There was a scene where Holmes

425
00:21:19,941 --> 00:21:22,341
showed a letter of that color to Watson.

426
00:21:22,341 --> 00:21:23,541
If I want to take a closer look at it,

427
00:21:23,541 --> 00:21:25,841
I'll have to take it out of the plastic bag.

428
00:21:25,841 --> 00:21:28,641
Huh? Is it in a plastic bag?

429
00:21:28,641 --> 00:21:31,269
-Yep. -Then, take the paper out of the bag

430
00:21:31,441 --> 00:21:33,041
and wet it with water!

431
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:36,341
The plastic bag is a hint that tells you to wet it!

432
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:44,541
The letters are fading because of the water.

433
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:47,541
Only the letter "S" is left clearly legible!

434
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:48,741
It seems that only the letter "S"

435
00:21:48,741 --> 00:21:50,841
is written with an oil based pen.

436
00:21:50,841 --> 00:21:55,293
Yeah! The paper is thick in order to hide this!

437
00:21:55,293 --> 00:21:56,441
If the paper is thin,

438
00:21:56,441 --> 00:21:58,641
only the letter that is written with an oil based pen will smear

439
00:21:58,641 --> 00:22:01,299
and all the way to the back of the paper.

440
00:22:01,541 --> 00:22:03,641
Which means...

441
00:22:03,641 --> 00:22:05,641
that the keyword for the St. Bride Church

442
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:07,641
that is shaped like a cake is...

443
00:22:07,641 --> 00:22:08,941
"S"!

444
00:22:08,941 --> 00:22:11,309
The egg-shaped City Hall is...

445
00:22:11,541 --> 00:22:12,641
"T"!

446
00:22:12,641 --> 00:22:16,041
The pickle shaped building Gherkin is...

447
00:22:16,041 --> 00:22:17,315
"N"!

448
00:22:17,315 --> 00:22:20,241
And the loud ringing sound of Big Ben...

449
00:22:20,241 --> 00:22:21,319
"A"!

450
00:22:21,541 --> 00:22:25,041
In the coded sentences Big Ben comes out twice,

451
00:22:25,041 --> 00:22:27,341
so I guess we can say that the letter "A" will appear twice.

452
00:22:30,941 --> 00:22:32,641
Satan!

453
00:22:32,641 --> 00:22:34,641
It's the devil.

454
00:24:01,419 --> 00:24:03,440
Next Conan's Hint:

455
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,220
"Saturn"

456
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:08,958
Shinichi, who's more important to you, me or Holmes?

457
00:24:08,958 --> 00:24:11,100
Why, that's obvious. Of course it's...

